### STRONG-003 : Ownership check systématique

**Règle** : Vérifier l'ownership avant modifications sur ressources utilisateur.

```python
# ✓ PRÉFÉRÉ
@router.patch("/{entity_id}")
async def update_entity(
    entity_id: UUID,
    data: EntityUpdate,
    user_id: UUID = Depends(get_current_user_id)
):
    entity = await service.get_by_id(entity_id)
    
    if entity.owner_id != user_id:
        raise HTTPException(
            status_code=403,
            detail="You can only update your own entities"
        )
    
    return await service.update(entity_id, data)

# Alternative : ownership check dans service
@router.patch("/{entity_id}")
async def update_entity(
    entity_id: UUID,
    data: EntityUpdate,
    user_id: UUID = Depends(get_current_user_id)
):
    return await service.update(entity_id, data, user_id=user_id)
    # Service lève PermissionError si ownership invalide
```

